<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="257" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/524</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Iranian Minister</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schayesteh</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 501</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-03">June 3,
                                1942</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Minister of Iran presents his compliments to His Excellency the
                            Secretary of State and has the honor to bring to his attention the
                            following:</p>
                        <p>The Iranian Government desires to engage in this country an American
                            financial expert in Government Finance. He should have a broad knowledge
                            and experience in the financial field.</p>
                        <p>The Minister of Iran would appreciate it very much if the Honorable the
                            Secretary of State would find and suggest a suitable candidate for this
                            position.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>